# CSS Rules

- Prefer component-scoped `styles.module.css` files for custom component styles.
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for layout, spacing, typography, and simple visual treatment when that keeps markup readable.
- Use CSS modules for component-specific styling that would be awkward, repetitive, or overly dense in utilities.
- Keep selectors simple, local, and easy to trace back to the component.
- Use shared CSS variables and existing tokens before introducing new hardcoded values.
- Use nested PostCSS syntax when it makes modifier and state styles easier to read.
- Keep global styles in `src/styles/` limited to tokens, typography, shared utility classes, and true global overrides.
- Keep stylesheets focused; if a component needs substantial unique styling, colocate it with that component.
